<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
    <aura:set attribute="title" value="Aura-Specific Types"/>

    <p>This table lists the supported type values for types that are specific to Aura.</p>

    <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>type</th>
                <th>Example</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td><code>Aura.Component</code></td>
                <td>N/A</td>
                <td>A single Aura component. We recommend using <code>Aura.Component[]</code> instead.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
                <td><code>Aura.Component[]</code></td>
                <td><code>&lt;aura:attribute name="detail" type="Aura.Component[]"/&gt;</code>
                    <p>To set a default value for <code>type"Aura.Component[]"</code>, put the default markup in the body of <code>aura:attribute</code>. For example:</p>

<auradocs:codeblock>
&lt;aura:component&gt;
    &lt;aura:attribute name="detail" type="Aura.Component[]"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;default paragraph1&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/aura:attribute&gt;
    Default value is: <aura:text value="{!"/>v.detail}
&lt;/aura:component&gt;
</auradocs:codeblock>
                </td>
                <td>Use this type to set blocks of markup. For more information, see <auradocs:topicLink topic="helloFacets">Component Body and Facets</auradocs:topicLink>.</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
                <td><code>Aura.Action</code></td>
                <td><code>&lt;aura:attribute name="onclick" type="Aura.Action"/&gt;</code></td>
                <td>Use this type to pass an Aura action to a component.</td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Using Aura.Action</h2>

    <p>A <code>Aura.Action</code> is a reference to an action in Aura. You can pass a <code>Aura.Action</code> around so the receiving component can execute the action in its client-side controller. Use <code>run()</code> to execute client-side controller actions, and <code>$A.enqueueAction()</code> to execute server-side controller actions.</p>

    <auradocs:info>Note: The underlying value object for an attribute of type <code>Aura.Action</code> is <code>ActionReferenceValue</code>.</auradocs:info>

    <p>The Aura Note sample app uses <code>Aura.Action</code> in the <ui:outputURL value="https://github.com/forcedotcom/aura-note/blob/master/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/components/auranote/listRow/listRow.cmp" label="listRow.cmp">listRow.cmp</ui:outputURL> component.</p>

    <p><b>listRow.cmp</b></p>

<auradocs:codeblock>&lt;aura:component extensible="true"&gt;
   ...
   &lt;aura:attribute name="onclick" type="Aura.Action"/&gt;
   ...
   &lt;li onclick="<aura:text value="{!"/>v.onclick}"&gt;
       ...
   &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/aura:component&gt;
</auradocs:codeblock>

    <p>The <code>onclick</code> attribute has <code>type="Aura.Action"</code>.</p>

    <p><b>noteListRow.cmp</b></p>

<auradocs:codeblock>&lt;aura:component extends="auranote:listRow"&gt;
    ...
    &lt;aura:set attribute="onclick" value="<aura:text value="{!"/>c.openNote}"/&gt;
   ...
&lt;/aura:component&gt;
</auradocs:codeblock>

    <p>The <ui:outputURL value="https://github.com/forcedotcom/aura-note/blob/master/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/components/auranote/noteListRow/noteListRow.cmp" label="noteListRow.cmp">noteListRow.cmp</ui:outputURL> component extends listRow.cmp and sets the value for the <code>onclick</code> attribute in <code>listRow.cmp</code> to <code><aura:text value="{!"/>c.openNote}</code>, which is a reference to an action in the client-side controller for <code>noteListRow.cmp</code>. The action is executed when a user clicks the bullet associated with <code>&lt;li onclick="<aura:text value="{!"/>v.onclick}"&gt;</code> in <code>listRow.cmp</code>.</p>

</aura:component>
